	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This weapon is certainly worth the time it takes to complete this brief quest. I am a Level 9 Dwarf Paladin and he went down fast, plus he spawned quickly. I read all of the comments and gathered that killing the other 'obsolete models' to get Red V to spawn quicker, and so I did. He will try to get outside as soon as he realizes that he isn't going to win. The best preparation for this is to attack an 'obsolete model' before Red V and remember that path that it takes to try to get out. All of the creatures and models go the same way. <BR>
<BR>
Manik was hard to find because only one of the comments about this weapon/quest contain directions for finding him. He is a silvery armored guy in Ak'Anon in the hall near the Warrior Guild (#14 on the map of Ak'Anon). Red V spawns in the back right corner to the left of the 3 Wizard-like people hanging around in a round room. Kill the gnome-like 'obsolete models' and get a bunch of the metal bits that they leave behind. When you kill Red V he will give you a box, combine 4 metal bits in the box and take it to Manik. <BR>
<BR>
What ever you do, don't attack the skeletons. That is the surest way to die because they get protected by the wizards in the tunnels. I would recommend getting bound near the enterance of the tunnels because you are probably going to attack something that you shouldn't and get killed. Even casting a spell on a skeleton got me killed. The good news is that you can go through the tunnels after that and get your corpse without the people who killed you before remembering to kill you again.<BR>
<BR>
This quest is well worth it and I highly recommend it to anyone who wants a great 1HB weapon. I am on Brell Serelis server and so if you need any help getting this, please let me know.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
