	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				My character performing this quest is an 11th level Dwarven cleric.  My faction to Manik began as indifferent.  It took me 7 tries to get the Bullsmasher (lucky me!).  I believe that it is totally random as to Manik's drop of the weapon.  I got Iony's (sp?) Sphere on the first try.<BR>
<BR>
Here are my observations:<BR>
<BR>
- The non-skeletal creatures in the mines are placeholders for the obsolete models.  I noted two spawn areas at (approx.) 2226,-390 and 2045,-580 while I was alone in the mines (early in the day).  I was also on during a peak period, and there were more creatures roaming around.  I think they are also PH's for obsoletes.<BR>
<BR>
- Faction doesn't matter (except you may have to be able to just talk to Manik).  I was indifferent at the start and end of the quest.<BR>
<BR>
- The Red V placeholder does spawn 6 minutes after the previous placeholder's death.<BR>
<BR>
- Recommendations:  Get a lot of backpacks (keep an open slot for the original incomplete box), get bound near Manik or near Red V (if you have Gate), spend time killing non-skeletal creatures (the cash does add up after a while), examine the armor you may get as a reward closely (I found that sometimes it was better than my leather stuff I had on.), and BE PATIENT.<BR>
<BR>
Grolan<BR>
Priest of Brell<BR>
11th Season<BR>
Rallos Zek
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
