			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Here is my 2 CPs on this great item.  After about 10 hours trying, I finally got a hammer.  I killed Red V about 12 times and it looked like 12 was the magic number for me, but who knows.<BR>
<BR>
Twp things I did want to add.<BR>
<BR>
1) I found that if you run around the maze and kill all the other Clockworks (not the merchants, just the Obselete ones) and the Rock spiders, Red V spawns faster.  I dont know why, but it was what I did halfway through the camping (out of boredom) and I noticed Red spawned more often.  I am not saying that is the truth, but take it as it is.  Heck, what else are you going ot do.<BR>
<BR>
2) The other thing I did was to buy a sewing kit and use all the spiderling silks that I could pick up.  I went from having no skill to 17 over the course of the camping.  Again, it was something to pass the time with.<BR>
<BR>
Good luck to you.  The weapon is worth it.<BR>
<BR>
Horkins Pumpkinpot<BR>
Lvl 20 Halfling Cleric<BR>
Drinal Server
